  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the membership base and improve production.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Currently the cooperative has 134 members but there is a big number of coffee farmers in this particular area which are non-members and the big number of non-members sell their produce to the cooperative. Twongerekawa Coko is aiming at increasing and strengthening the membership base looking at gender balance.It is located in Gakenke District -Northern Province.It sources its coffee from a total of 1 306 coffee farmers from this District known for the premium coffee quality.
The cooperative collects coffee cherries from coffee producers during the harvest season  takes it to the coffee washing station and does wet processing. The processing is done following quality standards by separating good cherries from low quality cherries (immature  picked by insects  or other defects) using floating methods  fermentation and cleaning pulp and mucilage until the cooperative gets dried parchment.

As the cooperative is selling the green coffee to international buyers  they go through a hulling process and follow Rwanda exports regulation as guided by National Agriculture Export Development Board(NAEB) and export institutions. 
The cooperative is the newest member of Misozi coffee company and has sold an equivalent of 3 Containers of coffee in 2016. The cooperative sells all coffee with help from Misozi.
In 2019 various mobilisation events will be conducted to encourage women and youth to join the cooperative. It is expected to double the number of cooperative members  in 2019 .The cooperative on the value chain side has committed to improve their production by training coffee farmers on the coffee  quality control and use of organic manure to boost and sustain their business.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">During this project seven activities were planned
Project activities
-Mobilisation of new members
-Mobilization of youth
-Training on quality coffee control
-Exchange visit to Karongi Coffee farmers
Advisory services and training
-Follow up -Skills implementation on financial management Supervisory board training and Organic coffee farming ToT</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening membership base and mobilise more youth for future sustainability of the cooperative.</narrative>
  </description>
